<li id="cite_note-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Doctrine and Covenants, <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_102#32" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 102">Section 102&#58;32</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">From 1961 to 2012, every member of the Presiding Bishopric had been called to be a general authority in another capacity upon being released from the Presiding Bishopric. Most have become Assistants to the Twelve or members of the First Quorum of Seventy; <a href="/wiki/Robert_D._Hales" title="Robert D. Hales">Robert D. Hales</a> was called as member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles. In 2012, <a href="/wiki/H._David_Burton" title="H. David Burton">H. David Burton</a> and his counselors were released and designated as emeritus general authorities.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Quorums_of_the_Seventy-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Quorums_of_the_Seventy_5-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation cs2"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/church/leaders/quorums-of-the-seventy?lang=eng">"Quorums of the Seventy"</a>, Organization, <i>LDS Church</i><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved <span class="nowrap">2013-03-14</span></span></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=LDS+Church&amp;rft.atitle=Quorums+of+the+Seventy&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fchurch%2Fleaders%2Fquorums-of-the-seventy%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGeneral+authority" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMonson2004" class="citation cs2"><a href="/wiki/Thomas_S._Monson" title="Thomas S. Monson">Monson, Thomas S.</a> (May 2004), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/ensign/2004/05/the-sustaining-of-church-officers">"The Sustaining of Church Officers"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Ensign_(LDS_magazine)" title="Ensign (LDS magazine)">Ensign</a></i>: 24</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Ensign&amp;rft.atitle=The+Sustaining+of+Church+Officers&amp;rft.pages=24&amp;rft.date=2004-05&amp;rft.aulast=Monson&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas+S.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fensign%2F2004%2F05%2Fthe-sustaining-of-church-officers&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGeneral+authority" class="Z3988"></span>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFFlake2001" class="citation cs2">Flake, Lawrence R. (2001), "Members of the Quorum of the Twelve Called By Each President of the Church", <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://rsc.byu.edu/archived/prophets-and-apostles-last-dispensation/members-quorum-twelve-called-each-president-church"><i>Prophets and Apostles of the Last Dispensation</i></a>, Provo, Utah: <a href="/wiki/Religious_Studies_Center" title="Religious Studies Center">Religious Studies Center</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>, pp.&#160;321–322</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Members+of+the+Quorum+of+the+Twelve+Called+By+Each+President+of+the+Church&amp;rft.btitle=Prophets+and+Apostles+of+the+Last+Dispensation&amp;rft.place=Provo%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pages=321-322&amp;rft.pub=Religious+Studies+Center%2C+Brigham+Young+University&amp;rft.date=2001&amp;rft.aulast=Flake&amp;rft.aufirst=Lawrence+R.&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Frsc.byu.edu%2Farchived%2Fprophets-and-apostles-last-dispensation%2Fmembers-quorum-twelve-called-each-president-church&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGeneral+authority" class="Z3988"></span>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This practice had become more flexible for a period of time when <a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Gordon B. Hinckley</a> was church president.  For example, as of the October 2004 General Conference, three of the seven members of the Presidency of the Seventy, two other members of the First Quorum, and four members of the Second Quorum were aged 70 or more and continued in office.  During the administration of <a href="/wiki/Thomas_S._Monson" title="Thomas S. Monson">Thomas S. Monson</a>, the typical pattern described has been used.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The April 2012 release of <a href="/wiki/H._David_Burton" title="H. David Burton">H. David Burton</a> and his counselors was an exception to this, as they were simply designated as emeritus general authorities, rather than members of the First Quorum.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Doctrine and Covenants, <a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Doctrine_and_Covenants/Section_20#65" class="extiw" title="s:The Doctrine and Covenants/Section 20">Section 20&#58;65</a></span>
</li>
